reaction.Name: 20alpha22beta-hydroxycholesterol is cleaved by CYP11A1 to yield pregnenolone and isocaproaldehyde
Androstenedione is converted to estrone by Aromatase (CYP19A1)
Cholesterol is hydroxylated to 24-hydroxycholesterol by CYP46A1
Cholesterol is hydroxylated to 7alpha-hydroxycholesterol by CYP7A1
LTB4 is hydroxylated to 20oh-LTB4 by CYP4F24F3
Further hydroxylation of calcidiol in kidney to form calcitriol
Cholesterol is hydroxylated to 27-hydroxycholesterol by CYP27
CYP24A1 catalyzes the initial step in the deactivation of the hormonally active form of vitamin D3
11-deoxycortisol is oxidised to cortisol by CYP11B1
11-deoxycorticosterone is oxidised to corticosterone by CYP11B2
Dehalogenation of carbon tetrachloride to form a free radical
CYP2C18 initiates bioactivation of phenytoin by 4-hydroxylation
Dehalogenation of the poly-halogenated hydrocarbon Halothane to form the acylhalide Trifluoroacetlychloride and hydrogen bromide
Vinyl chloride is oxidized to 2-Chloroethylene oxide
CYP3A5 oxidises aflatoxin B1 to aflatoxin-89-oxide
PGH2 is isomerised to TXA2 by TBXAS1
PGH2 is isomerised to PGI2 by PTGIS
CYP26A1 breaks down all-trans-retinoic acid by 4-hydroxylation
CYP26B1 also deactivates all-trans-retinoic acid by 4-hydroxylation
